1.title: Bradley Cooper/Lady Gaga/Ryan Gosling/Jodie Whittaker/Rod Stewart
1.plot: Multi Oscar-nominated actor Bradley Cooper and pop superstar Lady Gaga talk about their hotly anticipated musical romance A Star Is Born (2018); English actress Jodie Whittaker discusses her role as The Doctor on the upcoming season of Doctor Who (2005); double Oscar-nominee Ryan Gosling talks about upcoming biopic First Man (2018) and playing astronaut Neil Armstrong; rock legend Rod Stewart performs his current single "Didn't I".

2.title: Rowan Atkinson/Jamie Lee Curtis/Gary Barlow/Jeff Goldblum
2.plot: Together on Graham's sofa tonight: comedy genius Rowan Atkinson, back in action in Johnny English Strikes Again (2018), American actress Jamie Lee Curtis, reprising her role as Laurie Strode in the new Halloween (2018), 40 years after the original; pop star Gary Barlow, talking about his autobiography "A Better Me"; and Hollywood king of cool Jeff Goldblum, who chats and performs "Straighten Up and Fly Right" with Irish singer-songwriter Imelda May.

3.title: Whoopi Goldberg/Harry Connick Jr./Rosamund Pike/Jamie Dornan/BTS
3.plot: Graham's guests tonight are veteran comedian, actor and writer Whoopi Goldberg, talking about her stand-up comedy show, The Fall (2013) and Fifty Shades of Grey (2015) star Jamie Dornan, promoting My Dinner with Hervé (2018), Oscar-nominated actress and star of Gone Girl (2014) Rosamund Pike, who is starring in biographical drama A Private War (2018), and singer and actor Harry Connick Jr.. With music from South Korean boy band BTS, who perform their hit song "Idol".

4.title: Michael Caine/Sally Field/Chris Pine/Rami Malek/Christine and the Queens
4.plot: Legendary actor Sir Michael Caine talks about his new book "Blowing the Bloody Doors Off and Other Lessons in Life"; two-time Academy Award winner Sally Field tells about her autobiography "In Pieces"; American actor Chris Pine promotes his upcoming historical action drama Outlaw King (2018); Mr. Robot (2015) star Rami Malek discusses his role as Freddie Mercury in biopic Bohemian Rhapsody (2018); French pop star Christine and the Queens performs "Five Dollars", off her new album "Chris".

5.title: Eddie Redmayne/Jude Law/Melissa McCarthy/Emma Stone/Rick Astley
5.plot: English actors Eddie Redmayne and Jude Law talk about their upcoming fantasy adventure Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald (2018); American comedian Melissa McCarthy tells about her more serious role in biographical drama Can You Ever Forgive Me? (2018); BAFTA, Golden Globe and Academy Award winner Emma Stone promotes her historical drama The Favourite (2018); pop icon Rick Astley performs his song "Try".

6.title: Kurt Russell/Claire Foy/David Walliams/Lee Evans/Mumford and Sons
6.plot: Iconic actor Kurt Russell talks about his upcoming Netflix Christmas movie The Christmas Chronicles (2018); The Crown (2016) star Claire Foy discusses her upcoming crime thriller The Girl in the Spider's Web (2018); British comedian and bestselling children's author David Walliams promotes his new book "The Ice Monster"; comedy legend Lee Evans talks about the Harold Pinter celebration "Pinter at the Pinter" in the West End; British folk band Mumford & Sons perform their new single "Guiding Light", off their fourth studio album "Delta".

7.title: Ian McKellen/Michael Bublé/Carey Mulligan/Taron Egerton
7.plot: Sir Ian McKellen joins Michael Bublé, Carey Mulligan and Taron Egerton on Graham Norton's couch.

8.title: Nicole Kidman/Stephen Fry/Joe Lycett/Geraint Thomas/Take That
8.plot: Australian Hollywood star Nicole Kidman talks about her two upcoming movies, crime thriller Destroyer (2018) and drama Boy Erased (2018); actor/writer/comedian Stephen Fry discusses his new novel "Heroes", the follow-up to "Mythos"; comedian Joe Lycett promotes his new stand-up comedy DVD "I'm About to Lose Control and I Think Joe Lycett Live"; 2018 Tour de France winner Geraint Thomas talks about his career and book "The Tour According to G: My Journey to the Yellow Jersey"; British pop group Take That perform "Greatest Day", off their new greatest hits album "Odyssey".

1.plot: Graham is joined by The Devil Wears Prada (2006) and The Girl on the Train (2016) star Emily Blunt and American The Office (2005) star John Krasinski, who appear together in new horror movie A Quiet Place (2018), and Tom Holland, who is reprising the role of Spider-Man in new Marvel film Avengers: Infinity War (2018). Pop star and actress Kylie Minogue performs her new single "Stop Me from Falling" from her album "Golden".

2.title: Dwayne Johnson/Naomie Harris/Martin Freeman/Roger Daltrey
2.plot: Graham's guests are wrestler-turned-actor Dwayne Johnson and Oscar-nominated star of Moonlight (2016) and the James Bond series Naomie Harris, starring together in monster movie Rampage (2018), and Sherlock (2010) star Martin Freeman, appearing in horror anthology Ghost Stories (2017). Legendary rocker Roger Daltrey performs his new single "As Long as I Have You".

3.title: Benedict Cumberbatch/Matt LeBlanc/Maxine Peake/Calvin Harris feat. Dua Lipa
3.plot: Graham is joined by Oscar nominee Benedict Cumberbatch, playing Dr. Strange in Avengers: Infinity War (2018), actor/presenter Matt LeBlanc, playing himself in the final series of Episodes (2011), and English actress Maxine Peake, playing a 70s club comedian in Funny Cow (2017). Plus music from Calvin Harris featuring Dua Lipa, performing their new single "One Kiss".

4.title: Orlando Bloom/Tamsin Greig/Stephen Merchant/SuRie
4.plot: Among the guests on Graham's sofa are actor Orlando Bloom, comedian Stephen Merchant and actor Tamsin Greig. Plus music from SuRie, performing the UK's Eurovision entry Storm.
